Hvg.hu: How did you choose the six singers?
Why exactly you, what was the guiding principle?
B. Zs.: The basic idea was to make a gospel-like choir.
Then came the idea to compose the choir from gifted soloists of the local music scene.
This is how the six-piece choir came into being - Sena, Edina Kutzora, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Eniki Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - which we later named "Underground Divas".
hvg.hu: Did you want the song to be the same, or did the girls help shape it?
Zs: The song has been in the instrumental version for a long time, but when the material for the album was finished, we thought that this song still "needs something".
The chord sequence has formally demanded a singing voice.
I sang the melody the same night, later they learned the girls.
Everything was practically straightforward and terrifyingly spontaneous.
I remember I was quite electrified at the time, but the "Divas" were already needed.
With my voice alone, the song would never have become so powerful.
hvg.hu: Both on the record and at the concert you had the impression that the girls were in the background.
There’s no solo part (apart from Judy Jay’s short solo), they don’t have their own role, sing perfectly together and are no louder than the music, so their singing isn’t just accompanied by the music.
They were also on the back stage.
Is it intentional?
B.Zs.: The fact that they stood behind was because of purely technical problems.
However, we deliberately did not want to give them solo roles.
The number is also about forgetting your ego a bit, forgetting who came from where and where to go, let’s just let these particular wings, the wings of love, lift us up.
I would like others to feel this euphoric state that we felt when the song came into being.
Hvg.hu: What was the most elaborate song?
B. Zs.: In the musical creative work actually none, there have been more difficult tasks in mixing.
For example, with "Dorian Gray's Dilemma", in which I play on a concert keyboard, or with "Rock'n'Roll Goes To The Girls", where the groove didn't work any longer, but gradually everything came together as if it were a puzzle.
hvg.hu: What is your favorite song from the new album?
B. Zs.: This is constantly changing with the concerts and even now that I have the album "let go".
Currently, it's "Prophet Is A Fool", "Escape From The Earth" and the song "Never The Same".
