After the Aviation and Defense Group has announced that it will have to spend between 1.2 and 1.4 billion euros to counteract the residues of the A400M, the EADS share is currently showing a significant decline on the Paris Stock Exchange.
EADS currently loses 4% to 21.96 euros on the Paris Stock Exchange.
The group was forced to reconsider its business forecasts for 2007, referring to the residues caused by the slow progression of the engine of the A400M, which delayed the aircraft's maiden flight.
The cost announced in October to offset the delay in delivery of their military transport aircraft is between 1.2 and 1.4 billion euros, of which more than one billion for Airbus, announced the parent company of European manufacturer EADS.
