On Thursday, the UMP and Nouveau Centre groups refused to discuss the articles of the socialist bill on purchasing power, which is equivalent to rejecting the text.
The text, created as part of a socialist niche (meeting on the initiative of a parliamentary group), stated about ten measures that had been adopted by the National Committee of the PS on Wednesday, the majority of which were 50% for the employment allowance, the reintroduction of the TIPP floatante, a transport check or the limitation of rents.
