Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible loss caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of preparation of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right vehicle insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to submit the corresponding compensation amount in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that is composed of several factors, including age, gender, time of preparation of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that if there is a higher risk of accidents, higher contributions will also be due.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and thus also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefit that is attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his or her personal needs.
We now list the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance policy, in order to be able to make not only a performance-oriented but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as the low driving practice and the young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out a full-cash insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full-casco with deductible, so that the services of a full-casco insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract involves the customer having to pay a portion of the amount incurred by the damage itself.
The amount will be determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s chief representative at First Europa, a broker for online insurance.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against damage caused to their own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a piece of advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to reduce insurance costs; this way your credit will increase by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction of the basic rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and fines depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a high-yield year behind it, it may allow itself to increase bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to enter into a contract. This is due to the fact that as driving practice increases, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most sensible to opt for a full-cash insurance with equity.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the beginner's anxiety has been removed.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out full insurance; of course, only if it also allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contributions are low.
In this case, a full-cash insurance with deductible (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which only starts in the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to set a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full-cash insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it is important to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accidental damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection that fits our personal situation.
