A change in U.S. private insolvency laws in 2005 led to an abrupt case of bankruptcy filings, which in turn accounted for a large part of the kedit card losses; the number of filings (and thus default fees) would increase again, whether the general terms for borrowers are deteriorating or not.
Industry also reports solid payment rates showing how much of its debt consumers pay off every month
and trust in credit card-based securities is quite strong, despite the standstill in other corners of structured financing.
